The Player Card is a nice image that you can use as a signature on different sites and forums. It shows your
up-to-date account stats. An an excellent way to show-off with your account!
<br><br>

<!-- Player Card Image Display -->
<div class="centerp">
    <% if (hasPlayerCard) { %>
        <img src="/images/myplayercard/<%= userId %>.jpg?t=<%= Date.now() %>" alt="My Player Card"
            style="border: 1px solid #999;">
        <br><br>
        Join The Naruto Online Multiplayer Game Naruto - Arena.com
    <% } else { %>
        <p><i>You haven't generated a player card yet. Use the form below to generate one!</i></p>
    <% } %>
</div>

<br><br>

<!-- Player Card Options Form -->
<form method="post" action="/my-player-card/update">
    <fieldset style="border: 1px solid #999; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
        <legend style="font-weight: bold;">Player Card Options</legend>

        By checking/unchecking this checkbox your player card will show/hide your last 3 characters.
        <br><br>

        <table class="max">
            <tbody><tr class="color1">
                <td width="180"><b>Show characters:</b></td>
                <td><input type="checkbox" class="nb" name="show_characters" id="show_characters" <% if (showCharacters) { %>checked<% } %>></td>
            </tr></tbody>
        </table>
    </fieldset>

    <br>

    <!-- Update Button -->
    <div class="centerp">
        <input type="submit" class="button" value="Update Player Card">
    </div>
</form>

<br><br>

<!-- Site/BB-Code Section -->
<fieldset style="border: 1px solid #999; padding: 10px;">
    <legend style="font-weight: bold;">Site/BB-Code</legend>

    You can use the player card as your signature on sites/forums by simply copy/pasting the following code:
    <br><br>

    <table width="100%" cellspacing="10">
        <tr>
            <td width="50%" valign="top">
                <b>HTML-Code:</b><br>
                <textarea rows="5" cols="25" readonly
                    style="font-size: 10px;">&lt;a href="/profile/<%= user %>"&gt;&lt;img src="/images/myplayercard/<%= userId %>.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</textarea>
            </td>
            <td width="50%" valign="top">
                <b>vB-Code:</b><br>
                <textarea rows="5" cols="25" readonly
                    style="font-size: 10px;">[URL="/profile/<%= user %>"][IMG]/images/myplayercard/<%= userId %>.jpg[/IMG][/URL]</textarea>
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</fieldset>

